  m_text: "Dog anatomy refers to the structure of a dog\u2019s body, including its
    external features and internal systems. Externally, it includes parts like the
    head, ears, legs, tail, and coat. Internally, a dog\u2019s body is made up of
    systems such as the skeletal system (bones for support), muscular system (movement),
    circulatory system (heart and blood flow), respiratory system (lungs for breathing),
    digestive system (processing food), and nervous system (brain and nerves for
    control). All these systems work together to help the dog move, sense its environment,
    and maintain overall health."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
